getPassivePorts

java.lang.String getPassivePorts()
Get the passive ports to be used for data connections. Ports can be defined as single ports, closed or open ranges. Multiple definitions can be separated by commas, for example:
  • 2300 : only use port 2300 as the passive port
  • 2300-2399 : use all ports in the range
  • 2300- : use all ports larger than 2300
  • 2300, 2305, 2400- : use 2300 or 2305 or any port larger than 2400
Defaults to using any available port

Returns:
The passive ports string

A free passive part
